The paper introduces a new method for deep learning on graph structures, which is a popular topic in machine learning research. The paper specifically focuses on the ability to quantify uncertainty in deep learning on graph structures, which suggests a strong connection to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the ability to extend graph neural networks to inputs of dynamic sized graphs, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper uses conditional neural processes as a starting point, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses edge imputation, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper uses graph neural networks, which suggests a connection to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
